metadata.name: Louise
metadata.description:
It was one of the first snowfalls before Louise froze for the winter. My timing was serendipitous. I arrived first thing in the morning, approximately 6:30 am. The lake was like glass, the snow untouched. It was incredibly peaceful, in every sense of the word; physically, mentally, spiritually. It was one of those mornings where everything lined up perfectly.

Iâ€™ll never forget that morning with Louise.
